\begin{abstract}

Privacy-preserving range queries over encrypted Industrial
Internet of Things (IIoT) data have been widely studied;
however, existing schemes primarily focus on secure retrieval
and provide limited support for conjunctive multi-range
search, encrypted aggregation, and verifiable result
validation. In practical IIoT environments, operators require
multi-dimensional range queries together with authenticated
statistical analytics over outsourced encrypted sensor data.
To address these challenges, we propose
\emph{Blockchain-based Verifiable Conjunctive Range Search
and Aggregation (BVCRSA)}, a unified framework for secure
and verifiable analytics over encrypted IIoT data. BVCRSA
organizes encrypted records using an authenticated
hierarchical range-cover index that combines logarithmic
canonical interval decomposition with protected bitmap
filtering and cross-dimensional intersection for scalable
conjunctive range evaluation. The framework integrates
attribute-based searchable encryption with Threshold
EC-ElGamal homomorphic aggregation, enabling fine-grained
access control and direct encrypted computation over matched
records without granting users an aggregation private key.
BVCRSA further introduces blockchain-anchored query-state
verification that combines Merkle-authenticated search
structures, bitmap commitments, and authenticated batch
commitments to provide authenticated query-state integrity,
completeness, freshness, and rollback resistance without
zero-knowledge proofs or trusted hardware. Experimental
results demonstrate efficient trapdoor generation,
practical bitmap-based query processing, low verification
overhead, and substantial aggregation benefits compared
with representative searchable range-query schemes on
their common functionalities.

\end{abstract}

\begin{IEEEkeywords}
IIoT, ABSE, Range Query, Conjunctive query, Data Aggregation, Edge Computing, Bitmap index, Blockchain.
